        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-06-28T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-06-28T19:00:00-05:00" n="399" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d399">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894A.00/6–2549: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-06-28T20:00:00-04:00">June 28, 1949—8 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1303. Dept appreciative suggestion urtel 2490 June 25, rptd Canton as 802, but
                    believes no useful action feasible these lines at this time.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
